          "settings": {
            "question": "3. Are Hydrafacial treatments safe for sensitive skin?",
            "answer": "Yes. Hydrafacial treatments are widely considered suitable for sensitive skin because they are fully customizable. Providers can adjust treatment intensity, select gentler solutions and tailor boosters based on individual skin needs. The treatment is designed to improve concerns like dryness, congestion, uneven tone and visible redness without harsh exfoliation, making it a comfortable option for many sensitive skin types. As always, a consultation with a certified Hydrafacial provider helps ensure the treatment is tailored appropriately for your skin."
          }
        },
        "faq_7UNr44": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "4. How often should I get a Hydrafacial?",
            "answer": "Most clients schedule Hydrafacial treatments about once a month to maintain hydration, clarity and overall skin health. Some people choose treatments every 2 – 3 months, while others may opt for more frequent sessions, such as every 1 – 2 weeks, when addressing specific concerns or working toward targeted results. Because Hydrafacial Treatments are gentle and fully customizable, a certified provider can recommend the ideal treatment cadence based on your skin type, goals and lifestyle."
          }
